tplinkPPPoEConfigMIB.name: tplinkPPPoEConfigMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

tplinkPPPoEConfigMIB.description: Private MIB for PPPoE Circuit ID configuration.

tpPppoeIdInsertionGlobalEnable.name: tpPppoeIdInsertionGlobalEnable
tpPppoeIdInsertionGlobalEnable.description: 0. disable 1. enable Enable/Disable the PPPoE Circuit-ID function.

tpPppoeIdInsertionPortConfigTable.name: tpPppoeIdInsertionPortConfigTable
tpPppoeIdInsertionPortConfigTable.description: A list of PPPoE Circuit-Id port config entries.

tpPppoeIdInsertionPortConfigEntry.name: tpPppoeIdInsertionPortConfigEntry
tpPppoeIdInsertionPortConfigEntry.description: An entry contains of the information of PPPoE Circuit-ID port config. Here you can configure the ports for the PPPoE Circuit-ID.

tpPppoeIdInsertionPortIndex.name: tpPppoeIdInsertionPortIndex
tpPppoeIdInsertionPortIndex.description: This object indicates the port number.

tpPppoeCircuitIdPortConfigEnable.name: tpPppoeCircuitIdPortConfigEnable
tpPppoeCircuitIdPortConfigEnable.description: 0. disable 1. enable Select Enable/Disable the PPPoE Circuit-ID Insertion feature for the port.

tpPppoeCircuitIdPortConfigIdType.name: tpPppoeCircuitIdPortConfigIdType
tpPppoeCircuitIdPortConfigIdType.description: 0. switch IP:The switch's IP address will be used to encode the Circuit-ID option. 1. switch MAC:The switch's MAC address will be used to encode the Circuit-ID option. 2. switch UDF:The user specified string with the maximum length of 40 will be used to encode the Circuit-ID option. 3. switch UDF-ONLY:Only the user specified string with the maximum length of 40 will be used to encode the Circuit-ID option. Select Circuit-ID type for the port.

tpPppoeCircuitIdPortConfigUdfValue.name: tpPppoeCircuitIdPortConfigUdfValue
tpPppoeCircuitIdPortConfigUdfValue.description: A user specified string with the maximum length of 40.

tpPppoeRemoteIdPortConfigEnable.name: tpPppoeRemoteIdPortConfigEnable
tpPppoeRemoteIdPortConfigEnable.description: 0. disable 1. enable Select Enable/Disable the PPPoE Remote-ID Insertion feature for the port.

tpPppoeRemoteIdPortConfigValue.name: tpPppoeRemoteIdPortConfigValue
tpPppoeRemoteIdPortConfigValue.description: A user specified string with the maximum length of 40.
